document_notes.text:
This update for mozilla-nss fixes the following issues:

Update to NSS 3.90.2:

- CVE-2023-5388: Fixed timing attack against RSA decryption in TLS (bsc#1216198)

notes.text: NSS was susceptible to a timing side-channel attack when performing RSA decryption. This attack could potentially allow an attacker to recover the private data. This vulnerability affects Firefox < 124, Firefox ESR < 115.9, and Thunderbird < 115.9.
